text: The Platymantis cagayanensis is a frog. It lives in the Philippines. People have seen it as high as 200 meters above sea level. The adult male frog is about 26.4-30.8 mm long from nose to rear end and the adult female frog is about 34.7-37.4 long. The frog is brown in color with dark spots, dark bars behind the eyes, and dark bars on the back legs. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Platymantis cagayanensis
